*** Building & Developing

The easiest way to build and develop Speedith is to install the NetBeans IDE:

    http://netbeans.org/

Or just download the Java SE version of NetBeans from here (make sure that you
have the JDK installed):

    http://netbeans.org/downloads/index.html



*** Dependencies

Right now Speedith depends on the following libraries:

    * iCircles (Inductive Circles), found here:

        http://git.gitorious.org/speedith/inductive_circles.git

    * Apache Commons CLI (Jakarta CLI), found here:

        http://commons.apache.org/cli/

    * ANTLRv3, found here:
    
        http://www.antlr.org/
